# ============================================================
# IMMOS — .gitignore
# ============================================================
#
# PURPOSE:
# This file is a security boundary, not just repo hygiene.
# Immigration data is among the most sensitive personal data
# that exists — passport details, visa history, refusal records,
# family situation, financial information, legal history.
#
# RULE: If in doubt, gitignore it.
# The system files (modes, prompts, structure) are public.
# Everything the user puts INTO the system is private.
#
# PHILOSOPHY:
# The harness is shareable. The data is never shareable.
# Git tracks the system. The system protects the data.
# ============================================================


# ============================================================
# REGISTRY — THE MOST SENSITIVE FILE IN THE SYSTEM
# Contains: passport details, visa history, refusal records,
# family situation, financial info, legal history.
# NEVER commit under any circumstance.
# ============================================================
registry/registry.yml


# ============================================================
# EVIDENCE INVENTORY
# Contains: document details, scores, expiry dates, file locations.
# Personal ammunition store — never commit.
# ============================================================
evidence.md


# ============================================================
# CASE TRACKING DATA
# Contains: active applications, deadlines, document status.
# User's live immigration situation — never commit.
# ============================================================
data/cases.md
data/documents.md
data/journal.md
data/*.db
data/*.tsv
data/*.csv


# ============================================================
# KNOWLEDGE FILES — FETCHED AT RUNTIME
# These are fetched fresh from official sources each session.
# They contain data specific to the user's situation.
# No value in committing — they regenerate on first launch.
# ============================================================
knowledge/us/
knowledge/ca/
knowledge/uk/
knowledge/last_update.json
knowledge/changelog.md

# Country packs (Phase 3): fetched cache is per-user data — never commit.
# pack.yml is the shareable asset (no personal data) — keep it tracked.
knowledge/countries/*/cache/

# Keep the sources index (this is system config, not user data)
!knowledge/sources.yml
# Keep country-pack contracts (system config / shareable asset)
!knowledge/countries/
!knowledge/countries/**/pack.yml

# ============================================================
# ADDING A NEW COUNTRY — MAINTENANCE RULE
#
# When the agent detects a new country in the user's registry
# (target_country or country_of_residence not yet in the knowledge
# base), it MUST add the country folder to this file BEFORE
# creating any knowledge files for that country.
#
# The agent handles this automatically in AGENTS.md Step 2a.
# If you are adding a country manually, follow this pattern:
#
#   knowledge/au/    ← Australia
#   knowledge/de/    ← Germany
#   knowledge/ie/    ← Ireland
#   knowledge/nz/    ← New Zealand
#
# Always use the 2-letter ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code.
# Also update knowledge/sources.yml and knowledge/last_update.json.
# Gitignore FIRST. Write knowledge files SECOND. Always.
# ============================================================


# ============================================================
# USER PROFILE CUSTOMIZATION
# User's personal preferences and agent notes.
# Never committed. Survives system updates exactly because
# it is never in git.
# ============================================================
modes/_profile.md


# ============================================================
# GENERATED REPORTS — PERSONAL BY NATURE
# Audit reports, challenge reports, readiness reports.
# Generated from registry and evidence — personal output.
# Keep the .gitkeep so the directory stays in git.
# ============================================================
reports/*.md
reports/*.pdf
!reports/.gitkeep


# ============================================================
# GENERATED DOCUMENTS — ATTORNEY BRIEFS, COVER LETTERS, ETC.
# Drafted documents contain personal details from the registry.
# Never commit — these are the user's private application materials.
# ============================================================
output/*
!output/.gitkeep


# ============================================================
# BUILDER PROMPTS — ONE-TIME USE
# These are bootstrap prompts used once to build the system.
# After the system is built they can be archived or deleted.
# If committed, archive them — they are not sensitive,
# just not needed in the running system.
# Uncomment these lines if you want to gitignore them:
# ============================================================
# BUILDER_AGENT.md
# CHERRY_AGENT.md
# SKILL_REGISTRATION_AGENT.md


# ============================================================
# CLI MEMORY AND LOCAL SETTINGS
# Agent memory written between sessions is personal.
# Local settings contain machine-specific config.
# ============================================================

# Claude Code
.claude/settings.local.json
.claude/memory/

# OpenCode
.opencode/settings.local.json
.opencode/memory/

# Antigravity CLI
.antigravitycli/settings.local.json
.antigravitycli/memory/

# Grok
.grok/settings.local.json
.grok/memory/

# Kimi
.kimi/settings.local.json
.kimi/memory/

# Qwen
.qwen/settings.local.json
.qwen/memory/

# Gemini CLI
.gemini/settings.local.json
.gemini/memory/


# ============================================================
# SECRETS — NEVER COMMIT
# API keys, tokens, credentials.
# Use .env.example as the template. Never commit .env.
# ============================================================
.env
**/.env.local
**/.env*.local
*.key
*.pem


# ============================================================
# BACKUP FILES
# Written by integrity scripts (normalize, dedup).
# Ephemeral — never commit.
# ============================================================
*.bak
*.backup
*.orig


# ============================================================
# SYSTEM HYGIENE
# ============================================================

# OS
.DS_Store
.DS_Store?
._*
Thumbs.db
ehthumbs.db
Desktop.ini

# Video and large media (never should be here)
*.mov
*.mp4
*.avi
*.mkv

# Node (if any scripts use it)
node_modules/
bun.lock
package-lock.json
**/*.tsbuildinfo

# Python (if any scripts use it)
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.pyo
.venv/
venv/

# Resolved prompts (ephemeral, created during startup)
.resolved-prompt-*

# Planning scratchpad (local only)
plan/
scratch/
notes/


# ============================================================
# WHAT IS NOT GITIGNORED — WHAT THE REPO TRACKS
# ============================================================
#
# AGENTS.md               — master brain (public system file)
# CLAUDE.md               — Claude Code wrapper
# GEMINI.md               — Gemini wrapper
# CODEX.md                — Codex wrapper
# README.md               — documentation
# modes/_shared.md        — character file (system logic)
# modes/intake.md         — mode files (system logic)
# modes/gap.md            — mode files (system logic)
# modes/timeline.md       — mode files (system logic)
# modes/pathway.md        — mode files (system logic)
# modes/draft.md          — mode files (system logic)
# modes/rfe.md            — mode files (system logic)
# modes/scan.md           — mode files (system logic)
# modes/batch.md          — mode files (system logic)
# modes/alert.md          — mode files (system logic)
# modes/verify.md         — mode files (system logic)
# modes/evidence.md       — mode files (system logic)
# modes/audit.md          — mode files (system logic)
# modes/readiness.md      — mode files (system logic)
# modes/attorney.md       — mode files (system logic)
# modes/challenge.md      — mode files (system logic)
# .agents/skills/         — skill registration (system logic)
# .claude/skills/         — skill registration (system logic)
# .antigravitycli/skills/ — skill registration (system logic)
# .grok/skills/           — skill registration (system logic)
# .kimi/skills/           — skill registration (system logic)
# .qwen/skills/           — skill registration (system logic)
# .opencode/commands/     — skill registration (system logic)
# knowledge/sources.yml   — official source index (system logic)
# registry/               — directory only (registry.yml ignored)
# data/                   — directory only (cases.md ignored)
# reports/                — directory only (reports ignored)
# output/                 — directory only (output ignored)
# docs/                   — all documentation
# *.gitkeep files         — preserve empty directories in git
#
# ============================================================
